{"cursor":"21904","size":15,"audio":[],"cat":[],"tmpl":[],"currentlang":"en","linknr":289,"url":"Science_wars","article":"The 'science wars' were a series of intellectual exchanges, between scientific\nrealists and postmodernist critics, about the nature of scientific theory which\ntook place principally in the United States in the 1990s. The postmodernists\nquestioned scientific objectivity, and critiqued the scientific method and\nscientific knowledge in cultural studies, cultural anthropology, feminist\nstudies, comparative literature, media studies, and science and technology\nstudies. The scientific realists countered that objective scientific knowledge\nis real, and that the postmodernist critics had little understanding of the\nscience they were criticising.\n","recorded":1362124697,"portal":[],"list":[],"links":"290","instances":["sociologist","academic","journal","science","international_relations","literature","magazine"],"pdf":["http://physics.nyu.edu/sokal/SocialText_reply_LF.pdf"],"categories":["Science and technology studies|Wars, Science","Historiography of science|Wars, Science","Critical theory","Criticism of postmodernism","Scientific controversies|Wars, Science","Ideological rivalry","Politics of science|Wars, Science"],"headings":["Historical background","The science wars","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"tags":[["objectivity","science"],["andrew_ross","academic"],["objectivity","science"],["steve_fuller","sociologist"],["objectivity","science"],["objectivity","science"],["andrew_ross","academic"],["objectivity","science"],["lingua_franca","magazine"],["steve_fuller","sociologist"],["objectivity","science"],["isis","journal"],["positivism","international_relations"],["objectivity","science"],["naturalism","literature"]],"image":["http://en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","http://bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-butto